text:
Shabree Lanesha Frett (born 1996 in British Virgin Islands) is a beauty pageant titleholder from the British Virgin Islands was crowned Miss British Virgin Islands 2020.
Frett obtained a Bachelors of Science in Communicative Sciences and Disorders (Speech Pathology) from the Alabama A&M University. She is currently works as an Executive Assistant at the H. Lavity Stoutt Community College.
Frett started her pageantry stint when she competed at Miss British Virgin Islands 2019. She placed as the 1st runner-up and lost to eventual winner Bria Smith. Later, Frett was appointed Miss Universe British Virgin Islands 2020. As the winner, Frett will represent her country at Miss Universe 2020.
